♪ ♪

00:12.512 --> 00:14.139
♪ MIGHTY ♪
- ♪ LA, LA, HEY ♪

00:14.222 --> 00:16.056
- ♪ MIGHTY ♪
- ♪ LA, LA, WOW ♪

00:16.140 --> 00:18.059
- ♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:18.143 --> 00:20.145
♪ I GOT THE BEAT,
SO ALL THE KIDS DANCE WITH ME ♪

00:20.228 --> 00:21.688
♪ ME, ME, ME ♪

00:21.771 --> 00:23.690
♪ STICK 'EM UP ALL AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B ♪

00:23.773 --> 00:24.357
♪ BEE, BEE, BEE ♪

00:24.441 --> 00:28.027
♪ ♪

00:28.111 --> 00:31.281
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:31.364 --> 00:33.324
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B ♪

00:46.129 --> 00:48.298
- GREETINGS, FELLOW HUMANIMALS.

00:48.381 --> 00:50.049
I'M RAINBOW, YOUR TOUR GUIDE,

00:50.133 --> 00:52.051
AND HERE AT THE
BORN TO BE WILDLIFE PRESERVE,

00:52.135 --> 00:55.096
ANIMALS ARE FREE
TO LET DOWN THEIR FUR.

00:55.180 --> 00:56.931
- OOH, MONKEYS!

00:57.015 --> 00:58.808
OVER HERE.

00:58.892 --> 01:00.101
COME ON; DON'T BE A LEMUR.

01:00.185 --> 01:02.604
SMILE, GUYS.

01:02.687 --> 01:04.980
UGH!
MANNERS.

01:07.484 --> 01:11.112
- THE PRESERVE STRIVES
TO PROTECT ENDANGERED SPECIES

01:11.196 --> 01:13.490
SUCH AS THE SNOW LEOPARD,
THE WHOOPING CRANE...

01:13.573 --> 01:14.991
- [coughs]
UNICORN.

01:15.074 --> 01:17.118
- THE GIANT PANDA, THE OCELOT--

01:17.202 --> 01:18.578
- [coughing]
UNICORN, UNICORN.

01:18.661 --> 01:19.829
- DO YOU HAVE SOMETHING
TO SHARE?

01:19.913 --> 01:22.081
- YES, I DO: THE TRUTH.

01:22.165 --> 01:23.833
YOU LEFT OUT UNICORNS,

01:23.917 --> 01:27.504
THE MOST EXTINCTISHEST
OF ALL EXTINCTISH ANIMALS.

01:27.587 --> 01:29.297
[laughter]

01:29.380 --> 01:31.257
- WHY AREN'T YOU LAUGHING?

01:31.341 --> 01:32.592
WE'RE MAKING FUN OF HER.

01:32.675 --> 01:33.593
HELP US.

01:33.676 --> 01:34.677
- OH, YEAH.

01:34.761 --> 01:36.513
[laughs weakly]

01:36.596 --> 01:37.847
- I DON'T SEE WHAT'S FUNNY

01:37.931 --> 01:40.725
ABOUT A POSSIBLE WORLD
WITHOUT UNICORNS.

01:40.809 --> 01:42.519
- THERE ARE NO WRONG BELIEFS,

01:42.602 --> 01:45.605
BUT YOURS ARE 100% INCORRECT.

01:45.688 --> 01:47.065
THERE ARE NO SUCH THINGS
AS UNICORNS.

01:47.148 --> 01:48.358
- OH, REALLY, RAINBOW?

01:48.441 --> 01:50.985
OF ALL PEOPLE, I WOULD THINK
SOMEBODY NAMED RAINBOW

01:51.069 --> 01:54.155
WOULD KNOW THAT UNICORNS
ARE VERY REAL.

01:55.698 --> 01:58.535
FACTS: UNICORNS ARE EVOLVED
FROM ZEBRAS AND REINDEER,

01:58.618 --> 02:01.496
EXCEPT THEY'RE SNOW WHITE
AND HAVE MAGICAL RAINBOW POWERS.

02:01.579 --> 02:03.373
THEY WERE HUNTED
TO NEAR EXTINCTION

02:03.456 --> 02:05.124
FOR THEIR SOLID GOLD HOOVES.

02:05.208 --> 02:07.794
AND THEY USED TO BE BFFs
WITH LIONS,

02:07.877 --> 02:10.213
BUT THERE WAS A FALLING OUT
OVER POLITICS A FEW YEARS AGO.

02:10.295 --> 02:12.799
- YOU'RE TURNING
A SEMIBORING TOUR

02:12.882 --> 02:14.843
INTO A TOTES BORING TOUR.

02:14.926 --> 02:17.887
- YEAH, STOP TALKING ABOUT
THE PRETTY, PRETTY UNICORNS.

02:17.971 --> 02:19.889
- I BELIEVE YOU, BESSIE.

02:19.973 --> 02:23.351
UNICORNS ARE ALIVE
IN OUR HEARTS, IN OUR MINDS--

02:23.434 --> 02:24.018
- AND IN REALITY!

02:24.102 --> 02:27.438
- NO, NEVER IN REALITY.

02:27.522 --> 02:28.439
- BUT, PENNY--

02:28.523 --> 02:30.775
- PLEASE.

02:30.859 --> 02:33.611
- I'LL PROVE YOU CYNICS WRONG!

02:33.695 --> 02:36.322
I HAVE UNICORN POWER
ON MY SIDE.

02:36.990 --> 02:38.950
[monkey shrieks happily]

02:39.033 --> 02:40.118
MONKEYS.

02:40.201 --> 02:43.955
HMM, BABY UNICORNS
ARE TECHNICALLY CALLED

02:44.038 --> 02:45.248
UNICORN BABIES.

02:45.331 --> 02:46.958
AH, A FUN FACT
BUT HARDLY THE EVIDENCE I NEED

02:47.041 --> 02:49.669
TO PROVE
THE WHOLE WORLD IS WRONG.

02:49.752 --> 02:51.004
crash!

02:51.087 --> 02:51.963
[doorbell rings]

02:52.046 --> 02:53.715
PLEASE BE A UNICORN!

02:56.759 --> 02:58.970
YES, PROOF!

02:59.053 --> 03:03.266
THE 100% AUTHENTIC UNICORN HORN
I BOUGHT ON bBAY.

03:03.349 --> 03:04.726
thunk!

03:04.809 --> 03:07.520
AH, LIGHT AND DURABLE
AS PLASTIC.

03:07.604 --> 03:09.814
- IT IS PLASTIC.

03:09.898 --> 03:12.108
- BE GONE, NAYSAYER!

03:12.191 --> 03:15.528
- TRUST ME,
I KNOW UNICORN HORNS.

03:15.612 --> 03:17.447
I'VE SEEN ONE UP CLOSE.

03:17.530 --> 03:19.741
- WHA--YOU'RE A BELIEVER?

03:19.824 --> 03:20.783
- YES,

03:20.867 --> 03:26.080
EVER SINCE MY ENCOUNTER.

03:31.252 --> 03:32.837
OOH!

03:32.921 --> 03:36.007
[unicorn whinnies]

03:41.971 --> 03:43.640
[farts]

03:44.766 --> 03:47.852
- WHOA!
YOU FART RAINBOWS.

03:47.936 --> 03:50.313
AND THEY SMELL
LIKE APPLE CINNAMON.

03:50.396 --> 03:52.190
- [giggles]

03:52.273 --> 03:52.649
- WHOA!

03:52.732 --> 03:57.070
[laughs]

04:15.380 --> 04:18.591
- YOU RODE A UNICORN?

04:18.675 --> 04:20.301
- I TOLD ALL MY FAMILY
AND FRIENDS,

04:20.385 --> 04:22.220
BUT EVERYONE SAID
IT WAS JUST A DREAM.

04:22.303 --> 04:26.516
PORTIA EVEN CALLED IT
A LAME DREAM.

04:26.599 --> 04:28.142
LOOK, HIGGENBOTTOM.

04:28.226 --> 04:30.478
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE PROVE
THESE HORNHEADS ARE REAL?

04:31.187 --> 04:33.356
OF COURSE, IF WE FAIL,

04:33.439 --> 04:36.150
YOU UNDERSTAND
I WAS NEVER HERE.

04:36.234 --> 04:38.695
- SO BASED ON OUR COMBINED YEARS
OF RESEARCH,

04:38.778 --> 04:40.530
IT SEEMS UNICORNS
MOST LIKELY LIVE

04:40.613 --> 04:42.240
IN COSTA RICA,

04:42.323 --> 04:44.200
NORTHERN DUBLIN,

04:44.283 --> 04:45.535
OR SOUTHEAST NEWARK.

04:45.618 --> 04:46.995
[unicorn whinnies]

04:47.078 --> 04:49.914
- SO HOW MANY B-BUCKS DOES
A PLANE TICKET TO DUBLIN COST?

04:49.998 --> 04:51.040
- OH!

04:51.124 --> 04:54.043
"TOO FAR.
GO BACK TO WHERE YOU STARTED."

04:54.127 --> 04:55.503
OH, AN UNEXPLAINABLE CLUE!

04:55.586 --> 04:56.462
I LOVE THESE.

04:56.546 --> 04:58.214
LET'S SEE.
HMM.

04:58.298 --> 04:59.757
WE WERE BOTH BORN
IN THE HOSPITAL,

04:59.841 --> 05:01.384
SO MAYBE THE UNICORNS
ARE HIDING OUT IN HOSPITALS.

05:01.467 --> 05:05.138
- WHAT, VOLUNTEERING
AS CANDY STRIPERS?

05:05.221 --> 05:06.639
- THAT IS NOT
A HELPFUL ATTITUDE.

05:06.723 --> 05:08.266
- OW!

05:08.349 --> 05:11.185
"NOT WHERE YOU WERE BORN,
WHERE YOU WERE HUMILIATED."

05:11.269 --> 05:12.186
OH, IT'S FOR YOU.

05:12.270 --> 05:15.398
- HMM, WHERE I WAS HUMILIATED.

05:15.481 --> 05:17.483
STILL NOT NARROWING IT DOWN.

05:20.153 --> 05:21.446
"THIS AFTERNOON."

05:21.529 --> 05:23.448
OH, OF COURSE!

05:23.531 --> 05:26.367
THE WILDLIFE PRESERVE.

05:29.537 --> 05:31.914
- [gasps]

05:31.998 --> 05:34.083
- [gasps]

05:37.336 --> 05:40.089
HEY, BUDDY, HAS YOUR COUSIN
THE UNICORN BEEN AROUND LATELY?

05:43.468 --> 05:44.761
FINE, BLOOD'S THICKER
THAN WATER.

05:44.844 --> 05:48.097
I GET IT.

05:48.181 --> 05:49.348
[horse snoring]

05:52.685 --> 05:54.228
- NOPE, NOT PAINT.

05:54.312 --> 05:56.314
HE'S REALLY BROWN.

05:56.397 --> 05:58.691
- AND NO HORN
UNDER THIS COMB-OVER.

05:58.775 --> 06:00.568
COME ON; LET'S RECHARGE.

06:07.366 --> 06:07.784
HERE, GWEN.
MY TREAT.

06:07.867 --> 06:10.369
[gasps]

06:16.375 --> 06:17.293
[camera shutter clicks]

06:17.376 --> 06:18.461
- WHERE'D IT RUN OFF TO?

06:18.544 --> 06:20.463
- I DON'T KNOW,
BUT CHECK THIS OUT.

06:20.546 --> 06:21.631
SEE THAT SHIMMER?

06:21.714 --> 06:23.466
TELL ME
THAT'S NOT UNICORN GLITTER.

06:23.549 --> 06:25.051
- OH, IT'S DEFINITELY
A UNICORN.

06:25.134 --> 06:28.304
NOBODY CAN CALL US CRAZY NOW.

06:28.387 --> 06:29.972
- YOU'RE CRAZY...NOW.

06:30.056 --> 06:31.349
TOTES CRAZY.

06:31.432 --> 06:33.059
- WHAT?
YOU CAN'T SEE IT?

06:33.142 --> 06:35.603
RIGHT THERE, THAT WHITE BLUR
IS A UNICORN.

06:35.686 --> 06:37.605
- OH, IT'S SAD, SO SAD.

06:39.899 --> 06:41.692
- I EXPECT THIS FROM MESSIE.

06:41.776 --> 06:43.903
BUT YOU, GWEN?

06:43.986 --> 06:45.238
I'M NOT SO MUCH MAD

06:45.321 --> 06:47.990
AS I'M, LIKE, TOTES DISAPPOINTED
AND GROSSED OUT.

06:48.074 --> 06:50.326
YOUR COOL POINTS
ARE SO REVOKED.

06:50.409 --> 06:51.994
PENNY!

06:52.078 --> 06:54.956
YOU'RE PROMOTED.

06:55.039 --> 06:56.332
- A BLURRY PHOTO'S
NOT GOOD ENOUGH, HUH?

06:56.415 --> 06:58.960
FINE, THE NEXT TIME
YOU SEE US,

06:59.043 --> 07:01.045
WE'LL BE RIDING A UNICORN...

07:01.129 --> 07:02.755
OR HOLDING A BETTER PHOTO.

07:02.839 --> 07:04.173
COME ON, GWEN.

07:04.257 --> 07:07.093
UGH, THIS IS THE SLEEPOVER
I'VE BEEN AVOIDING

07:07.176 --> 07:08.845
FOR THE LAST FIVE YEARS.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.429
- TECHNICALLY,
IT'S NOT A SLEEPOVER.

07:10.513 --> 07:12.640
IT'S A STAKEOUT.
NO SLEEP ALLOWED.

07:18.855 --> 07:20.273
[chiming]

07:20.356 --> 07:21.524
- [sniffs]

07:21.607 --> 07:23.109
IS THAT...APPLE CINNAMON?

07:23.192 --> 07:24.527
- [sniffs]

07:29.031 --> 07:32.410
both: UNICORN FARTS!

07:39.375 --> 07:41.127
- IT'S--IT'S--

07:41.210 --> 07:42.628
IT'S--

07:42.712 --> 07:43.671
- A UNICORN!

07:46.465 --> 07:47.967
AND HE'S INCARCERATED.

07:56.309 --> 07:58.519
- DON'T CRY, UNICORN.

07:58.603 --> 08:00.188
WE'RE BUSTING YOU OUT!

08:02.481 --> 08:03.566
[whistles]

08:12.617 --> 08:16.954
[triumphant music]

08:25.504 --> 08:26.297
- ILL-MANNERED MONKEYS!

08:26.380 --> 08:28.799
- IT'S ALWAYS MONKEYS.

08:28.883 --> 08:30.593
[laughing]

08:30.676 --> 08:32.929
- [gasps]

08:33.011 --> 08:35.514
PAPER AIRPLANES?
GLITTER?

08:35.597 --> 08:36.933
A RAINBOW PROJECTOR?

08:37.015 --> 08:38.267
APPLE CINNAMON BATHROOM SPRAY?

08:38.351 --> 08:41.437
A BRIGHT WHITE FLASHLIGHT?

08:41.520 --> 08:45.358
THE MONKEYS USED US TO BREAK OUT
OF THE WILDLIFE PRESERVE!

08:45.441 --> 08:48.152
WHAT'S THE MAPLE SYRUP FOR?

08:48.236 --> 08:50.905
[monkeys cackling]

08:52.073 --> 08:54.242
[buzzing]

09:01.290 --> 09:01.540
[both scream]

09:06.337 --> 09:07.797
- HELP!
LET US OUT!

09:07.880 --> 09:09.173
THIS ISN'T WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE!

09:09.257 --> 09:11.717
LOOK PAST THE FUR.
WE'RE HUMAN.

09:11.801 --> 09:12.843
HEY, WHAT WAS THAT FOR?

09:12.927 --> 09:16.597
- THIS IS ALL YOUR FAULT,
STINKENBOTTOM.

09:16.681 --> 09:18.099
- DON'T BLAME ME.

09:18.182 --> 09:19.976
YOU BELIEVE IN UNICORNS TOO.

09:20.059 --> 09:23.521
- YEAH, AND I WAS SMART ENOUGH
TO KEEP THAT A SECRET.

09:23.604 --> 09:25.022
- REALLY?
SMART ENOUGH?

09:25.106 --> 09:26.983
OR WERE YOU CHICKEN ENOUGH?

09:27.066 --> 09:28.276
- [gasps]

09:28.359 --> 09:29.652
- YEAH, I SAID IT.

09:29.735 --> 09:31.654
[clucking]

09:31.737 --> 09:33.447
- YOU CAN MAKE ME A MONKEY,

09:33.531 --> 09:35.741
BUT DO NOT CALL ME CHICKEN.

09:37.285 --> 09:40.413
[shrieking like monkeys]

09:47.753 --> 09:49.630
OH, WHAT'S THE POINT?

09:49.714 --> 09:52.008
RAINBOW FARTS WERE JUST A DREAM.

09:52.091 --> 09:56.178
UNICORNS ARE JUST TOO BEAUTIFUL
FOR THIS STINKIN' WORLD.

09:56.262 --> 09:58.889
- NO, DON'T SAY THAT.

09:58.973 --> 10:01.183
IF WE GIVE UP,
HOW WILL A UNICORN KNOW

10:01.267 --> 10:03.102
TO SWOOP DOWN AND SAVE US?

10:03.185 --> 10:05.646
- OH, LET IT GO.

10:05.730 --> 10:09.817
- PLEASE,
O MAGICAL AND PRETTY UNICORNS.

10:09.900 --> 10:12.194
DESCEND FROM YOUR SKY KINGDOM,
AND SAVE US.

10:12.278 --> 10:15.072
OR, AT THE VERY LEAST,
VISIT ALL THE HONEYBEES

10:15.156 --> 10:17.074
TO PROVE I WAS RIGHT.

10:21.620 --> 10:22.705
[birds chirping]

10:37.386 --> 10:39.263
both: WHOA!

10:47.855 --> 10:50.066
- THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR THE RESCUE.

10:50.149 --> 10:53.402
BUT CAN WE ASK YOU ONE MORE
TEENY, TINSY FAVOR?

11:01.744 --> 11:03.245
- YES!

11:03.329 --> 11:06.248
I CAN'T WAIT TO RUB THIS PROOF
IN PORTIA'S STUPID FACE.

11:06.332 --> 11:07.917
- GWEN, PLEASE.

11:08.000 --> 11:11.796
THERE'S NO REASON FOR US
TO SAY, "I TOLD YOU SO."

11:11.879 --> 11:12.963
JUST KIDDING!

11:13.047 --> 11:14.924
WE HAVE EVERY REASON
TO SAY, "I TOLD YOU SO."

11:15.007 --> 11:15.674
I MEAN, JUST LOOK
AT THESE PHOTOS.

11:18.677 --> 11:20.096
HEY, HMM, WELL,

11:20.179 --> 11:21.680
GLAD I TOOK MORE THAN ONE.

11:24.350 --> 11:25.351
[laughs nervously]

11:25.434 --> 11:29.063
AT LEAST WE HAVE OUR MEMORIES.

11:52.628 --> 11:54.130
- OKAY, YOU WERE RIGHT.

11:54.213 --> 11:56.173
IT IS MORE FUN WHEN I FETCH.

11:56.257 --> 11:58.217
NOW, COME ON.
THROW ME A ROCKET.

12:00.386 --> 12:02.138
- OW!

12:02.221 --> 12:05.808
NO, NOT MY NEW PONYTAIL!

12:05.891 --> 12:08.769
WANNA FETCH?

12:08.853 --> 12:12.565
THEN GO FETCH!

12:34.628 --> 12:35.921
AH!

12:37.423 --> 12:39.341
DROP IT, WEEDS.

12:39.425 --> 12:42.344
THIS NATURE IS TOO WILD.

12:42.428 --> 12:46.682
WHO'S IN CHARGE
OF CLEANING THIS UP?

12:46.765 --> 12:48.976
"YOU'RE IN CHARGE
OF CLEANING THIS UP.

12:49.059 --> 12:50.686
ADOPT A HIGHWAY."

12:50.769 --> 12:54.023
WELL, WHO AM I
TO ARGUE WITH A SIGN?

12:54.106 --> 12:57.109
HAPPY, WE'RE ADOPTING A HIGHWAY.

12:58.444 --> 13:01.697
- [muttering angrily]

13:01.780 --> 13:04.074
- YOU GOT A LOT
ON YOUR PLATE RIGHT NOW?

13:05.451 --> 13:09.455
FINE. I'LL RAISE THIS HIGHWAY
ON MY OWN.

13:13.792 --> 13:14.877
HA, THERE.

13:14.960 --> 13:17.004
HUMAN TRASH GONE.

13:17.087 --> 13:19.173
NOW IT'S TIME TO GET RID
OF NATURE'S TRASH:

13:19.256 --> 13:21.967
WEEDS.

13:33.312 --> 13:36.148
[cuckoo clock cuckooing]

13:41.737 --> 13:43.030
[motor roaring]

13:49.161 --> 13:49.995
[glass shattering]

13:59.547 --> 14:02.258
MUSIC STING.

14:02.341 --> 14:05.261
[dramatic music]

14:05.344 --> 14:14.728
♪ ♪

14:14.812 --> 14:17.398
[weeds scream]

14:18.399 --> 14:20.985
HOW DO YOU LIKE ME NOW?
YEAH, WEEDS?

14:21.068 --> 14:23.153
HOW DO YOU LIKE ME NOW?

14:23.237 --> 14:26.365
AND NOW THE MAKEOVER.

14:26.448 --> 14:29.451
[lively band music]

14:29.535 --> 14:38.294
♪ ♪

14:42.590 --> 14:45.009
- THAT'S A MIGHTY FINE HIGHWAY
YOU GOT HERE.

14:45.092 --> 14:46.093
- WHY, THANK YOU.

14:46.176 --> 14:47.970
WEED FREE
SINCE YESTERDAY AT 3:00.

14:48.053 --> 14:50.889
AND SINCE YOU'RE
OUR FIRST PASSERBY...

14:50.973 --> 14:54.268
- OOH, TOFFEE
AND A COUPON BOOK.

14:55.936 --> 14:58.480
- REMEMBER, IT'S HIGHWAY 61,
MILE MARKER 19!

14:58.564 --> 15:00.774
PLEASE COME AGAIN, AND TELL
YOUR FRIENDS ABOUT US!

15:03.736 --> 15:07.281
- BEAUTIFUL GARDEN.

15:07.364 --> 15:08.282
- OOH, MAY I STOP
AND SMELL YOUR ROSES?

15:08.365 --> 15:11.160
- UH-HUH.

15:15.372 --> 15:18.626
- I LIVE IN SEATTLE,
BUT I HAD TO SEE IT MYSELF.

15:18.709 --> 15:21.003
IT WAS WORTH EVERY MILE!

15:23.881 --> 15:27.134
[vehicles honking]

15:29.470 --> 15:32.097
- WHAT?

15:32.181 --> 15:34.058
A FONT MESE?

15:36.185 --> 15:40.022
MOMMY! I WANT PEOPLE
TO HONK AT ME!

15:40.105 --> 15:41.899
- HMM, WE HAVE BEEN LOOKING
FOR A WAY

15:41.982 --> 15:45.486
TO GET YOUR FACE OUT THERE.

15:45.569 --> 15:49.198
- "SO JACK CHOPPED DOWN
THE BEAN STALK WITH HIS AX."

15:49.281 --> 15:55.996
OH, THEY'RE SUCH ANGELS
WHEN THEY'RE ASLEEP.

16:04.630 --> 16:05.631
GAH!

16:05.714 --> 16:07.675
PORTIA'S A GIANT!

16:07.758 --> 16:11.011
HAPPY'S NIGHTMARE CAME TRUE!

16:11.095 --> 16:14.848
WAIT, IT'S JUST AN AD
OVERLOOKING MY GARDEN.

16:14.932 --> 16:15.015
NO BIGGIE.

16:17.643 --> 16:20.562
MY GARDEN!

16:20.646 --> 16:23.691
HEY, PORTIA, NICE FACE,
INSANE SIZE.

16:23.774 --> 16:25.859
BUT--AND I MEAN THIS
WITH NO OFFENSE--

16:25.943 --> 16:27.569
YOU'RE GIANT FACE
IS ON MY BILLBOARD,

16:27.653 --> 16:29.905
KILLING MY GARDEN,
SO TEAR IT DOWN NOW, RIGHT NOW.

16:29.988 --> 16:32.783
- UH, I KNOW YOU'RE NOT TRYING
TO TELL ME WHAT TO DO

16:32.866 --> 16:33.826
WITH <i> MY</i> BILLBOARD.

16:33.909 --> 16:34.493
"A," YOU LOOK CRAZY.

16:34.576 --> 16:36.203
"B," AND SWEATY.

16:36.286 --> 16:40.666
THREE, THIS BILLBOARD
IS ALREADY TOTES MINE.

16:40.749 --> 16:42.084
MOMMY ADOPTED IT FOR ME.
SEE?

16:42.167 --> 16:45.713
- WHAT? YOU ADOPTED
THE HIGHWAY NEXT TO MINE?

16:45.796 --> 16:47.715
- DUH.

16:48.841 --> 16:50.759
AND AS YOU CAN SEE,

16:50.843 --> 16:53.429
THE BILLBOARD IS HERE,
ON MY LAND,

16:53.512 --> 16:56.807
WHICH MEANS
YOU ARE TOTES TRESPASSING.

16:56.890 --> 16:59.601
SO STEP OFF, MESSIE.

16:59.685 --> 17:00.978
- BUT--BUT--

17:01.061 --> 17:02.980
YOU STOLE MY SUNSHINE.

17:03.063 --> 17:04.606
- BORED NOW.
TALK TO THE BILLBOARD.

17:04.690 --> 17:06.483
[camera shutter clicks]

17:06.567 --> 17:07.151
HOT.

17:07.233 --> 17:09.194
- OF ALL THE NERVE.

17:09.278 --> 17:12.281
YOU DO NOT COME BETWEEN A MOTHER
AND HER ADOPTED HIGHWAY.

17:12.364 --> 17:14.867
OH, I'LL SHOW YOU.
I'LL SHOW YOU.

17:29.089 --> 17:31.091
- I WILL NOT BE UPSTAGED
BY A HEAT LAMP.

17:40.476 --> 17:41.810
- DO YOU NOT UNDERSTAND
HOW HARD IT IS

17:41.894 --> 17:45.522
TO NURTURE A HIGHWAY ON MY OWN?

17:45.606 --> 17:46.982
I NEED CONSTANT SUN.

17:47.066 --> 17:49.151
I NEED TO PULL ANY WEEDS.

17:49.234 --> 17:51.236
WEEDS, PORTIA, WEEDS!

17:51.320 --> 17:53.238
DON'T SAY I DIDN'T WARN YA.

17:53.322 --> 17:56.617
- AS IF.

18:01.663 --> 18:04.500
- WHAT...IS...THAT?

18:04.583 --> 18:05.751
- TA-DA!

18:05.834 --> 18:06.502
RUNNING
WITH THE RAINBOW UNICORNS--

18:06.585 --> 18:07.628
THE RIDE!

18:07.711 --> 18:09.213
DO YOU LOVE IT?

18:09.296 --> 18:14.551
- YOU DO NOT EXPLOIT THE UNICORN
FOR PERSONAL GAIN.

18:14.635 --> 18:18.096
NOBODY WILL RIDE
THAT CHEAP MONSTROSITY.

18:18.180 --> 18:22.142
- I MUST RIDE
THAT CHEAP MONSTROSITY.

18:22.226 --> 18:23.519
- HA!

18:23.602 --> 18:24.937
WELL, I SUPPOSE
THERE'S AN AUDIENCE

18:25.020 --> 18:27.189
FOR TACKY THEATRICS.

18:36.240 --> 18:37.241
OH, COME ON!
REALLY?

18:37.324 --> 18:41.078
WOULDN'T YOU FOLKS RATHER UNWIND
AT MY--

18:41.161 --> 18:41.787
[gasps]

18:41.870 --> 18:44.748
- WHATEVER, MESSIE.

18:44.832 --> 18:46.500
WALK AWAY.

18:46.583 --> 18:47.835
- OH, I'LL WALK AWAY.

18:47.918 --> 18:50.504
BUT I WILL NOT WHATEVER.

18:50.587 --> 18:53.924
IT'S ON.

19:03.976 --> 19:06.937
WHO WANTS TO RIDE MY LOG FLUME?

19:07.896 --> 19:08.146
[car alarm beeps]

19:15.028 --> 19:17.114
- LASER LIGHT SHOW.

19:21.952 --> 19:25.581
- OLD-TIME COUNTRY JAMBOREE.

19:25.664 --> 19:29.209
- KARAOKE CAR WASH.

19:29.293 --> 19:33.255
- DRIVE-IN MOVIE THEATER/
SUNDAE BAR.

19:38.802 --> 19:39.761
- ♪ HER NAME'S PORTIA, PORTIA ♪

19:39.845 --> 19:43.390
♪ PORTIA, PORTIA,
PORTIA, PORSH ♪

19:43.473 --> 19:46.977
{\an5}♪ PORTIA, PORTIA,
PORTIA, PORSH ♪

19:47.060 --> 19:48.145
♪ HER NAME'S PORTIA, PORTIA ♪

19:48.228 --> 19:50.731
♪ PORTIA, PORTIA,
PORTIA, PORSH ♪

19:50.814 --> 19:57.446
- 173, 174, 175, 176--

19:57.529 --> 20:01.116
UGH!
SHE'S BEATING ME BY ONE VISITOR.

20:01.199 --> 20:02.618
LOOKS LIKE
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO BUILD

20:02.701 --> 20:05.287
THAT COTTON CANDY BOUNCE HOUSE
AFTER ALL.

20:05.370 --> 20:07.122
- [screams]

20:07.205 --> 20:09.291
- YEAH, YEAH, THE SUGAR BOYZ
ARE DREAMY.

20:09.374 --> 20:10.334
I GET IT.

20:10.417 --> 20:12.669
- [screams]

20:18.508 --> 20:20.218
- I DON'T WANT TO SAY,
"I TOLD YOU SO,"

20:20.302 --> 20:22.471
BUT YOU GOT TO GIVE IT TO ME
ABOUT THE WEEDS.

20:27.643 --> 20:28.936
NEVER MIND.
HELP ME.

20:32.814 --> 20:35.484
AH! THESE WEEDS
ARE GROWING LIKE WEEDS.

20:35.567 --> 20:36.526
- GET OUT OF HERE.

20:36.610 --> 20:39.154
NOBODY EVEN LIKES YOU, WEEDS.

20:40.197 --> 20:41.114
[buzzing noise]

20:41.198 --> 20:42.950
WAIT, IS THAT MY--

21:06.431 --> 21:08.684
[both cheering]

21:14.606 --> 21:17.150
THANKS FOR THE SAVE, HAPS.

21:17.234 --> 21:21.154
I KNEW, DEEP DOWN, YOU WANTED
TO BE A FATHER TO THIS HIGHWAY.

21:23.281 --> 21:24.324
NO?

21:24.408 --> 21:25.492
THEN WHY ARE YOU HERE?

21:27.452 --> 21:28.996
OH, A LETTER FROM CITY HALL.

21:29.079 --> 21:30.455
LET'S SEE.

21:30.539 --> 21:31.498
THEY'RE REVOKING
OUR HIGHWAY ADOPTIONS

21:31.581 --> 21:34.501
FOR CAUSING
TOO MANY TRAFFIC JAMS.

21:34.584 --> 21:36.336
- DUH, OF COURSE
WE STOPPED TRAFFIC.

21:36.420 --> 21:37.921
WE'RE AWESOME.

21:38.630 --> 21:40.424
WELL, I'M AWESOME.

21:40.507 --> 21:43.552
- NO, YOU CAN'T TAKE AWAY
MY HIGHWAY!

21:43.635 --> 21:46.930
IT'S MY PRIDE AND JOY.

21:49.433 --> 21:50.809
- WELL, THEN DON'T BE
THE MESSENGER

21:50.892 --> 21:52.769
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO BE BLAMED
FOR STUFF.

21:52.853 --> 21:54.896
- NO, CITY HALL'S RIGHT.

21:54.980 --> 21:56.815
WE NEGLECTED OUR HIGHWAYS.

21:56.898 --> 21:57.691
AND FOR WHAT?

21:57.774 --> 22:00.235
FAME? UNICORNS?
SHAME ON US.

22:00.318 --> 22:03.905
HAPPY, THIS LAND
MAY BE YOUR LAND,

22:03.989 --> 22:06.074
BUT THIS LAND IS NOT MY LAND.

22:06.158 --> 22:09.036
HERE ARE ITS KEYS.

22:12.372 --> 22:13.623
- WHATEVS.

22:13.707 --> 22:15.709
I DON'T EVEN WANT
THIS STUPID HIGHWAY ANYMORE.

22:15.792 --> 22:17.627
THE SUN IS TOTES TOO HOT.

22:17.711 --> 22:18.670
I WANT TO GO TANNING.

22:18.754 --> 22:21.465
- AT LEAST WE WIPED OUT
ALL THE WEEDS.

22:23.050 --> 22:26.470
OKAY, OKAY, WE'RE GOING.

22:26.553 --> 22:29.848
YOU DON'T HAVE TO ESCORT US
OFF THE PROPERTY.

